  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description：</strong></u></p><ul><li>Coordinating and Reporting with Manager and Team Members</li><li>Motivating personnel to high performing standards and Excellence</li><li>Responsible for all construction activities of Construction Works for the Project</li><li>Ability to plan the sequence of works</li><li>Ensure that all the works are executed in accordance with approved Method Statement, Safety Procedure and Quality Methods</li><li>Arrange and Conduct Daily Tool Box Talk, Control the labor force(or sub contractor) with his assistance of Supervisor or foreman</li><li>Prepare Daily, Weekly and Monthly progress reports and submit to CM</li><li>In charge in the Inspection of Works and necessary approval by client side (QPS)</li><li>If require any traffic, utility or such as diversion which is under his responsible and control in due time with safe manner</li><li>Material Control</li><li>Ability to use AUTOCAD for amending shop drawing</li><li>Checking BBS which sent by Sub-con and co-ordinating with supplier until delivered to site</li><li>Preparation of RFI for ongoing Construction works</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirement:</strong></u></p><ol><li>Preferably with LTA experience and familiar with LTA procedure</li><li>Possess good analytical and communication skills</li><li>Diploma Civil Engineering or related field</li></ol>",
